==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outgaze
<hw>Out*gaze"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To gaze beyond;
to exceed in sharpness or persistence of seeing or of looking; hence, to
stare out of countenance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outgeneral</ent>⟦br⟧
